==English==
===Etymology===
From {{F.}} '''''[[interpréter]]''''', {{L.}} '''''[[interpretari]]''''', past participle '''''[[interpretatus]]''''', from '''''[[interpre]]''''' interpreter, [[agent]], [[negotiator]]; '''''[[inter]]''''' between + (probably) the root of '''''[[pretium]]''''' [[price]].

===Noun===
'''interpreter''' (''plural:'' '''[[interpreters]]''')

#One who [[interpret|interprets]].
## One who listens to a speaker in one language and relates that utterance to the audience in a different language.  Contrasted with [[translator]].
##: ''Wei Li had to interpret the whole speech, and they didn't even give her any study materials beforehand.''
## One who explains something, such as an art exhibit.
#(''Computing'') A [[program]] which [[execute]]s another program written in a [[programming language]] other than machine code.

